{"title_page": "Cl\u00e9o de Verberena", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Cleo de Verberena\n| image              = File:Cleo de Verberena revista Cinearte n\u00b0 221 1930.png\n| birth_name         = Jacira Martins da Silveira\n| birth_date         = 26 June 1904\n| birth_place        = [[Amparo, S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| death_date         = 6 October 1972\n| death_place        = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| occupation         = Actress, film director, film producer\n| father             = Jos\u00e9 Martins Ribeiro Jr.\n| mother             = J\u00falia Pereira da Silveira\n| children           = C\u00e9sar Augusto Melani\n| citizenship        = Brazilian, Chilean\n}}\n\n'''Jacyra Martins da Silveira''' (26 June 1904 \u2013 6 October 1972), known by her stage name '''Cleo de Verberena''', was a Brazilian actress and film director. She is widely considered as the first Brazilian woman to direct a film: 1931's ''[[O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto]]''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b-B9AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA209 |title=Brazilian National Cinema|last=Shaw|first=Lisa|last2=Dennison|first2=Stephanie|date=|publisher=Routledge|year=2014|isbn=9781134702107|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://memoria.bn.br/DocReader/docreader.aspx?bib=162531&pasta=ano%20193&pesq=verberena|title=A primeira directora do Cinema brasileiro|year=1930|website=memoria.bn.br|publisher=Cin\u00e9dia, n.221|page=10|language=Portuguese|trans-title=The first woman director of Brazilian Cinema|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nJacyra Martins Silveira was born on June 26, 1904, in the city of [[Amparo, S\u00e3o Paulo|Amparo]]. During the 1920s she moved to [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]. She fell in love with cinema; her favorite directors were [[Erich von Stroheim|von Stroheim]] and [[Fred Niblo]], and her favorite actress was [[Greta Garbo]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5GmWs7KHLycC&pg=PA559 |title=Dicion\u2021rio mulheres do Brasil: de 1500 at\u00e9 a atualidade : com 270 ilustra\u00e7\u00f5es|last=Schumaher|first=Schuma|last2=Brazil|first2=Erico Vital|date=2000|publisher=J. Zahar|isbn=9788571105737|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nThere she met Cesar Melani, the son of \u00c2ngelo Melani and Amabile Facci, landowners of [[Franca]], with whom she would eventually marry and have one child, Cesar Augusto. In 1930, they founded their studio, EPICA-FILM, in the district of Santa Cecilia, in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html|title=Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil|last=Baliego|first=Gabriella|date=October 2017|work=Caixa de Sucessos|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref> Jacyra adopted the artist name Cl\u00e9o de Verberena, and Melani called himself Laes Mac Reni.\n\nEPICA-FILM's first and only production was ''O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto'' (The Mystery of the Black Domino)<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Grecco de Araujo|first=Marcella|date=2020|title=Through versions of The Mystery of the Black Domino (1931)|url=http://www.socine.org/wp-content/uploads/anais/AnaisDeTextosCompletos2019(XXIII).pdf|journal=Anais de Textos Completos do XXIII Encontro SOCINE|volume=|pages=784-791|via=}}</ref>, based on the novel written by Martinho Correa. The feature movie was directed by and starring Cl\u00e9o de Verberena; her husband also worked in the production and as actor. Cleo also worked on stage plays with the ViaL\u00e1ctea group during 1931. \n\nIn 1932 she moved with her family to Rio de Janeiro to promote ''O Mist\u00e9rio'' and to try to find some work in the industry. Her participation at the movie industry was, although, restricted to O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto. She didn't have any other participation in movies. \n\nCesar Melani died in 1935 and Jacyra did not get involved with cinema anymore. She married a few years latter the Chilean consul Francisco Landestoy Saint Jean, moving with him to England and then Chile. Francisco died in 1953. Cleo, no longer married, settled in S\u00e3o Paulo with his son Cesar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html|title=Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil|work=Caixa de Sucessos|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref>\n\nCleo died on October 6, 1972, in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nCleo de Verberena, Brazilian pioneer, is the subject of the doctoral thesis of Marcella Grecco de Araujo, from University of S\u00e3o Paulo. <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Grecco de Araujo|first=Marcella|date=2019|title=Cleo de Verberena: uma cineasta brasileira|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gYat1pU9KnWaiD0uCV4E03w5sAst_XP7/view|journal=Revista Movimento|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Grecco de Araujo|first=Marcella|date=2019|title=Cleo de Verberena Profile|url=https://wfpp.columbia.edu/pioneer/cleo-de-verberena/|journal=Women Film Pioneers Project|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|1218437}}\n*[https://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil]\n\n[[Category:1904 births]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n[[Category:Actresses from S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n[[Category:Women film pioneers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian women film directors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Cleo de Verberena\n| image              = File:Cleo de Verberena revista Cinearte n\u00b0 221 1930.png\n| birth_name         = Jacira Martins da Silveira\n| birth_date         = 26 June 1904\n| birth_place        = [[Amparo, S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| death_date         = 6 October 1972\n| death_place        = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Brazil\n| occupation         = Actress, film director, film producer\n| father             = Jos\u00e9 Martins Ribeiro Jr.\n| mother             = J\u00falia Pereira da Silveira\n| children           = C\u00e9sar Augusto Melani\n| citizenship        = Brazilian, Chilean\n}}\n\n'''Jacyra Martins da Silveira''' (26 June 1904 \u2013 6 October 1972), known by her stage name '''Cleo de Verberena''', was a Brazilian actress and film director. She is widely considered as the first Brazilian woman to direct a film: 1931's ''[[O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto]]''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b-B9AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA209 |title=Brazilian National Cinema|last=Shaw|first=Lisa|last2=Dennison|first2=Stephanie|date=|publisher=Routledge|year=2014|isbn=9781134702107|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://memoria.bn.br/DocReader/docreader.aspx?bib=162531&pasta=ano%20193&pesq=verberena|title=A primeira directora do Cinema brasileiro|year=1930|website=memoria.bn.br|publisher=Cin\u00e9dia, n.221|page=10|language=Portuguese|trans-title=The first woman director of Brazilian Cinema|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nJacyra Martins Silveira was born on June 26, 1904, in the city of [[Amparo, S\u00e3o Paulo|Amparo]]. During the 1920s she moved to [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]. She fell in love with cinema; her favorite directors were [[Erich von Stroheim|von Stroheim]] and [[Fred Niblo]], and her favorite actress was [[Greta Garbo]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5GmWs7KHLycC&pg=PA559 |title=Dicion\u2021rio mulheres do Brasil: de 1500 at\u00e9 a atualidade : com 270 ilustra\u00e7\u00f5es|last=Schumaher|first=Schuma|last2=Brazil|first2=Erico Vital|date=2000|publisher=J. Zahar|isbn=9788571105737|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nThere she met Cesar Melani, the son of \u00c2ngelo Melani and Amabile Facci, landowners of [[Franca]], with whom she would eventually marry and have one child, Cesar Augusto. In 1930, they founded their studio, EPICA-FILM, in the district of Santa Cecilia, in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html|title=Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil|last=Baliego|first=Gabriella|date=October 2017|work=Caixa de Sucessos|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref> Jacyra adopted the artist name Cl\u00e9o de Verberena, and Melani called himself Laes Mac Reni.\n\nEPICA-FILM's first and only production was ''O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto'' (The Mystery of the Black Domino), based on the novel written by Martinho Correa. The feature movie was directed by and starring Cl\u00e9o de Verberena; her husband also worked in the production and as actor. Cleo also worked on stage plays with the ViaL\u00e1ctea group during 1931. \n\nIn 1932 she moved with her family to Rio de Janeiro to promote ''O Mist\u00e9rio'' and to try to find some work in the industry. Her participation at the movie industry was, although, restricted to O Mist\u00e9rio do Domin\u00f3 Preto. She didn't have any other participation in movies. \n\nCesar Melani died in 1935 and Jacyra did not get involved with cinema anymore. She married a few years latter the Chilean consul Francisco Landestoy Saint Jean, moving with him to England and then Chile. Francisco died in 1953. Cleo, no longer married, settled in S\u00e3o Paulo with his son Cesar.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html|title=Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil|work=Caixa de Sucessos|access-date=2017-11-01}}</ref>\n\nCleo died on October 6, 1972, in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nCleo de Verberena, Brazilian pioneer, is the subject of the doctoral thesis of Marcella Grecco de Araujo, from University of S\u00e3o Paulo. <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Grecco de Araujo|first=Marcella|date=2019|title=Cleo de Verberena: uma cineasta brasileira|url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gYat1pU9KnWaiD0uCV4E03w5sAst_XP7/view|journal=Revista Movimento|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Grecco de Araujo|first=Marcella|date=2019|title=Cleo de Verberena Profile|url=https://wfpp.columbia.edu/pioneer/cleo-de-verberena/|journal=Women Film Pioneers Project|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|1218437}}\n*[https://www.caixadesucessos.com.br/2017/08/cleo-de-verberena-primeira-cineasta.html Cl\u00e9o de Verberena - a primeira cineasta mulher do Brasil]\n\n[[Category:1904 births]]\n[[Category:1972 deaths]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n[[Category:Actresses from S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n[[Category:Women film pioneers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian women film directors]]\n", "name_user": "Magrecco", "label": "safe", "comment": "I inserted a reference about her movie", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cl%C3%A9o_de_Verberena"}
